# Server (Go)

## Patterns

- Plugin hooks in `plugin.go`; HTTP routes in `api.go`
- Slash commands — `server/command/` package
- Solidtime HTTP client — `server/solidtime/` package
- KV Store — `server/store/kvstore/`; keys: `solidtime_token_{userID}`, `solidtime_org_{userID}`

## Slash command `/solidtime`

```
/solidtime connect <api_token>  → validate via Solidtime API → save to KV
/solidtime disconnect           → remove from KV
```

Responses are ephemeral (`CommandResponseTypeEphemeral`), unless a channel post is needed.

## API proxy

- Middleware `MattermostAuthorizationRequired` — required for all `/api/v1/*`
- Solidtime token loaded from KV Store by `Mattermost-User-ID`
- Without token — `401` with JSON `{"error": "not_connected"}`

## Configuration

```go
type configuration struct {
    SolidtimeServerURL string
}
```

Normalize URL (strip trailing slash) in `OnConfigurationChange`. Without URL — `OnActivate` returns an error and the plugin does not activate.

## Tests

- Mocks for KV Store and Solidtime client (`go.uber.org/mock`)
- Tests alongside code: `*_test.go`
